        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 2:47PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 247 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 20 miles south of Almo to 11 miles southwest of
Park Valley. Movement was east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Park Valley, Rosette, Yost, and Standrod.

This includes Utah Route 30 between mile markers 40 and 69.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
